If selected, metadata retrieved from files will be cached for further access.

Only files prefixed by a valid URI scheme will be cached, like for example public://. Files in the temporary:// scheme will never be cached. Specify here if there are any paths to be additionally excluded from caching, one per line. Use wildcard patterns when entering the path. For example, public://styles/*.
